  "body": "### Description\r\n\r\n*Type*: Bug\r\n\r\n*Summary*: \r\n\r\nWhen I delete 1-1 chat(s) with previously read messages I had with another contacts (so no Unread message counter displayed on Chat screen), after I log out and log back in - all deleted chats reappear and display all messages I had with the contacts, that were deleted, - like they were Unread.\r\nThe main issue is that we should not resurrect deleted 1-1 chats at all.\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nNo deleted 1-1 chat appears if to log out and log back in to account\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nPreviously deleted 1-1 chat appears if to log out and log back in to account\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\nOpen Status on Device1\r\nOpen Status on Device2\r\nCreate UserA on Device1\r\nCreate UserB on Device2\r\nUserA adds UserB in contacts.\r\nUserA sends message to UserB\r\nUserB navigates to 1-1 Chat with UserA to read the message.\r\nUserB navigates back to 'Chats' list. Confirm no unread messages counter present.\r\nUserB deletes the chat with UserA\r\nUserB logs out\r\nUserB logs back in and stays on Chats list.\r\n\r\nNOTE: the same for group chats and public chats\r\nthe same behavior is reproducible for `Leave  group chat`, not only for delete\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n* Status version: 19/03/2018 nightly\r\n* Operating System: Android, iOS\r\n\r\n#### Logs\r\nwe did have the same issue https://github.com/status-im/status-react/issues/2870",
